commit.message:
Add PIC parameter to fix builds for some platforms

On some platforms (such as UWP), the static library must have position independent code (PIC) to be included properly in a shared library.
Add missing #include <netinet/in.h> for internet-related constants

Meson: Simplify pkgconfig generator

- pkg_cdata is unused and should have been deleted completely
- libmicrodns should be passed as first positional argument and not in
  libraries: keyword argument.
- deps should not be specified as public requires, they are private
  dependencies and Meson will add them automatically, no need to mention
  them.

Windows: Require at least Vista

inet_ntop() and struct pollfd are available since Windows Vista, but
mingw requires to define _WIN32_WINNT.

Fixes: #46

Simplify generation of pkgconfig file

Use meson's pkgconfig module to generate the pkg-config file, rather
than using old-school autotools patterns.

Document strrcmp()

So we don't need to reverse-engineer what it does from reading the code.
The documentation and the argument names are from the Linux kernel.

Closes: #42
add GitHub CI job

mdns: Fix getifaddrs fallback

This primarily fix build & behavior on android which doesn't have
getifaddrs
meson.build: Bump version to 0.2.0

meson.build: Bump the soversion

We changed a functions signature and added a new one
mdns: Fix invalid cast warning

compat: Fix joining multicast group using IP_ADD_MEMBERSHIP

Fix #36

compat: Remove multicast_if type

It's always an unsigned integer, never a pointer
os_mcast_join: Rename mintf to intf_idx

mdns: ctx: Rename if_addr to intf_idx

Since it always contains the interface index now
examples: Fix the announce example
Update NEWS
examples: Fix announce callback

mdns: Expose an announce type to the announce callback

And allow the application to explicitely require an initial announce
packet. We now also expose a goodbye announce type, in order to
implement clean shutdown, and not wait for the TTL to expire
until our services are considered gone

rr: Provide the packet length even when it's 0

Otherwise a 0 length TXT packet would be invalid

mdns: Don't pass mdns_recv return to the announce callback

mdns_recv returns -1 on error and 0 on success, but we don't invoke the
callback when mdns_recv fails, so we were passing a useless parameter
always equal to 0.

mdns: announce: Let the application filter its service types

There is no easy way to support multiple service types otherwise.

meson.build: Bump version

Since the API semantic changed a bit

Add dual stack support

We now can pass NULL instead of an IPV4/IPV6 address to use both
mdns: Share bind() code with win32
mdns: win32: Fix interface filtering
mdns: win32: Give up if the selected adapter doesn't have an address

mdns: Use the appropriate multicast address for the protocol

Instead of the 1st which might be using a different protocol version

mdns: Fix interface index on win32

While IP_MULTICAST_IF used the index in network byte order, setsockopt
with MCAST_JOIN_GROUP uses the index in host byte order

mdns: Fix and simplify interface selection

Providing the interface index (which is the integer returned by
if_nametoindex for an IPV4 connection, and the content of
sockaddr_in6.sin6_scope_id for an IPV6 connection) is enough.
With this, we can remove the additional call to setsockopt(...,
IP_MULTICAST_IF)
